title: Notre Dame soccer, M'Kenna Murphy have experience on their side
text:
Complete Box Score Â» 
Notre Dame soccer goalkeeper M'Kenna Murphy needed a few seconds on Tuesday night after the win over Northwestern to figure out how many senior teammates she has this season. 
After some thought and some checking with coach Sue Aquilina, the answer was 11 seniors on the Notre Dame roster. 
Trying to count up the big senior class is a good problem to have for the Crusaders. 
"It does (help) because there is a lot of experience on the team," Murphy said about all the seniors. "But then we also have a lot of young players who are coming up who are taking everything in from the upperclassmen and who are working very hard at practice. And they deserve to be out there too." M'Kenna Murphy (Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com ) 
One of those young players is freshman forward Mikayla Bates , who scored both Crusaders goals in Tuesday night's 2-0 road win over Northwestern. 
It was Notre Dame's fifth straight victory with all of them being shutouts. 
"I think we're really getting a very good sense of team and we're all working with each other," Murphy said. "It brings in an all togetherness that shows on the field. And that is how we score and that's how we win." 
Murphy has played a big part in the Crusaders' recent defensive success. 
She did it again versus the Tigers, making eight saves. Murphy had a leaping save off a Northwestern corner kick with 24:11 left in regulation and showed off her vertical leap again just over a minute later when Emily Renner sent a free kick toward the net. 
As is a common theme with the Crusaders, Murphy has experience on her side. 
"M'Kenna is a very solid keeper," Aquilina said. "She's been playing varsity keeper since her freshman year so she's got the experience behind her."
